Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers
NEW DELHI , November 22 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Indian newspapers Sunday .
The Hindustan Times :
-- Patients in the Capital had a harrowing time as thousands of resident doctors Saturday began an indefinite strike in protest against the failure of the government to look into their demands .
The Sunday Times :
-- The United States has announced the demolition of the largest and most sophisticated human smuggling ring in America history in which some 7,200 Indian citizens have been illegally brought to the U.S.
The Statesman :
-- The Election Commissioner , G. V. G. Krishnamurthy , Saturday ordered the sealing of Delhi 's borders by Saturday evening as a precautionary move in view of the forthcoming Assembly elections .
The Economic Times :
-- Delhi may ban non-commercial diesel vehicles to reduce pollution in the capital .
